      "form_guide": "",
      "comment": "This one has taken a hit by scratchings, which plays right into the hands of CELTICS (4) who lived up to some nice trials to win impressively first-up at Bendigo then stepped up to 64 grade last time where he beat home all bar the handy Purple Streak. Again draws well here and can be prominent throughout. HEY JESSIE (5) was tested in Stakes grade after an impressive Bendigo win at big odds and while outclassed there, she's clearly taken no harm from it as her two jumpouts this time have been of a horse who looks poised to make a big return. THAT'SMONEYBROTHER (7) was hard to miss charging into third first-up over 1000m at Yarra Valley, which was the first start for Matt Laurie. Been back to the jumpouts since, so should be ready to peak. QUEENSBURY (2) wouldn't have really been a consideration prior to scratchings, but gets his chance to sneak a spot in the top four in the field of six.",
